There was a worker fixing the kitchen floor, and I pretended to be working from home, but in reality I was editing "Wanting More."
God, if only this damned file would open. (OneDrive is such a piece of garbage.)
*Hacker's voice* I'm in.
He started drilling, and the sound was super loud. Great.
I turned the air purifier to the maximum setting, which felt a bit aggressive, but I did actually smell sawdust, so it was justified. Plus, he was against wearing masks. And I really did need to protect myself, didn't I?
I really want to go back to sleep, but I can't sleep until he leaves.
Good news! Chapter four is finally edited!
Chapter five is very long, and it's super anxiety-inducing. Yay! It's so exciting.
Currently searching and replacing... ➡️ ellipsis, this chapter has 54 of them 😅
But I still have to stick to this. Most natural languages are incoherent, especially when people are emotionally excited.
The floor repairman is vacuuming, hoping this means he is about to finish.
He went out (it sounds like) cutting something. I sneakily took a look at the progress. There's still a lot of work to do :(
Chapter 5 still has 7 pages left. This is still my favorite chapter, and the manuscript is in pretty good shape, mainly just some formatting adjustments and minor edits for active voice and conciseness. But I really need to take a break, have a cup of tea, and that guy is still messing around in my kitchen.
He started vacuuming again. Hoping this is a good sign.
The kitchen floor repairman has left!
He told me that he quoted the repair cost for the entire floor, but the landlord is very cheap and only willing to pay for the repair of the rotten area at the entrance. It feels much better.
I was drinking tea in the garden, while the air purifier in the kitchen was working hard to purify the air in the room!
